pageContext.claim: “New Hampshire should have been won last time [in 2016], except we had a lot of people come in at the last moment, which was a rather strange situation. Thousands and thousands of people coming in from locations unknown. But I knew where their location was.”
pageContext.analysis: There's no evidence of voter fraud in New Hampshire in the 2016 election, or the conspiracy theory Trump is spreading here, that "thousands and thousands of people [were] coming in from locations unknown."
